transformations.description:
This SQL query extracts and transforms data from the master_agency_detail table.
 Filtering rows based on Field_Representative column.
-- Selecting ,renaming columns, handling null valeus, derived columns
transformations.name: SQ_Master_Agency_Detail

object.customQuery:
SELECT
    A."Agency_ID" AS agency_key,
    A."Agency_Code" AS agency_code,
    
    CASE
        WHEN A."Status" = 'Cancelled' THEN
            'Cancelled - ' || A."Agency_Name" || ' (' || "Agency_Code" || ')'
        ELSE
            A."Agency_Name" || ' (' || "Agency_Code" || ')'
    END AS agency_name,

    COALESCE(A."Agency_Address", 'Not Applicable') AS agency_address,
    COALESCE(A."Agency_City", 'Not Applicable') AS agency_city,
    COALESCE(A."Agency_State", 'Not Applicable') AS agency_state,
    COALESCE(A."Agency_City" || ' ' || A."Agency_State", 'Not Applicable') AS agency_city_state,
    COALESCE(A."Agency_Zipcode", 'Not Applicable') AS agency_zip_code,
    COALESCE(A."Field_Representative_Group", 'Not Applicable') AS field_representative_group,
    COALESCE(A."Field_Representative", 'All Other Sales Territory') AS field_representative,
    A."Agency_Appointed_Dt" AS agency_appointed_dt,
    A."Agency_Contact_Phone" AS agency_contact_phone,
    A."agency_alpha_workflow" AS agency_alpha_workflow,
    A."Sales_Territory" AS sales_territory,
    A."Field_Representative_State" AS field_representative_state,
    A."Agency_Contact_Fax" AS agency_contact_fax,
    A."Source_Cd" AS agency_source,
    A."Status" AS status,
    A."Agency_Mail_Address1" || ' ' || A."Agency_Mail_Address2" AS agency_mailing_address,
    A."Agency_Mail_City" AS agency_mailing_city,
    A."Agency_Mail_State" AS agency_mailing_state,
    A."Agency_Mail_Zipcode" AS agency_mailing_zip,
    A."Agency_Email1" AS agency_email1,
    A."Agency_Email2" AS agency_email2,
    A."Agency_Email3" AS agency_email3,
    A."Agency_Email4" AS agency_email4,
    A."Agency_Email5" AS agency_email5,
    A."Agency_Email6" AS agency_email6,
    A."Agency_Email7" AS agency_email7,
    A."Agency_Email8" AS agency_email8,
    A."Agency_Email9" AS agency_email9,
    A."Agency_Email10" AS agency_email10,
    A.row_effective_dt as agency_detail_rowstrtdt,
     A.Agency_Group_Nbr
FROM int_msgr.master_agency_detail AS A
WHERE A.Row_End_Dt = '9999-12-31' and Field_Representative is not null

transformations.description:
This SQL `SELECT` statement retrieves latest data from the `int_msgr.master_agencyGroup_detail` table, with the following summary:

It selects various columns from the table, such as agency group details including group name, ID, qualifying amount, and multiple email addresses. The `COALESCE` function is used to provide default values ('Ungrouped') for columns that might contain NULL values. Additionally, a `WHERE` clause filters the results to include only rows where the `Row_End_Dt` column has a specific value ('9999-12-31 00:00:00.000').
transformations.name: SQ_Master_AgencyGroup_Detail

object.customQuery:
SELECT 
COALESCE(G."Agency_Group_Nbr", 'Ungrouped')   AS agency_group,
COALESCE(G."Agency_Group_Name", 'Ungrouped')  AS agency_group_name,
G."Agency_Group_Id" AS agency_group_id,
G."Agency_Group_Name1" AS group_name1,
    G."Agency_Group_Name2" AS group_name2,
    G."Qualifying_Amount" AS qualifying_amount,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email1" AS agencygroup_email1,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email2" AS agencygroup_email2,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email3" AS agencygroup_email3,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email4" AS agencygroup_email4,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email5" AS agencygroup_email5,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email6" AS agencygroup_email6,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email7" AS agencygroup_email7,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email8" AS agencygroup_email8,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email9" AS agencygroup_email9,
    G."AgencyGroup_Email10" AS agencygroup_email10,
    G.row_effective_dt as agencyGroup_rowstrtdt
FROM
int_msgr.master_agencyGroup_detail G
where 
G."Row_End_Dt" = '9999-12-31 00:00:00.000'

fields.name: zip_code_completeness
fields.expression:
DECODE(TRUE,
IN(agency_zip_code, '-')=1 AND LENGTH(agency_zip_code)=10,0,
LENGTH(agency_zip_code)>=5 AND LENGTH(agency_zip_code)<=6,0,
1)

fields.name: agency_contact_phone_completeness
fields.expression:
DECODE(TRUE,
ISNULL(agency_contact_phone),1,
LENGTH(agency_contact_phone)=12 and IN(agency_contact_phone,'-'),0,
LENGTH(agency_contact_phone)=10,0,
1
)
